<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A device used to measure the <a title="Roller Setting" href="Roller_Setting">roller setting</a>, or the pressure that exists between two offset press ink or dampening rollers. A roller-setting gauge measures the amount of force generated when the device's metal strip is pulled through the nip of the two rollers being set. A roller-setting gauge can also be used in concert with less objective methods such as the <a title="Three-Strip Method" href="Three-Strip_Method">three-strip method</a> and the <a title="Folded-Strip Method" href="Folded-Strip_Method">folded-strip method</a>. 
</p>
